to provide actual information that is applicable to the project.

which works well.

Only the acknowledgement message could be made
more specific to our own app.

acknowledgement message of ExitCommand class.

The link should be updated to Mass Linkers user guide.
A command summary could be included for easy reference.
Changing the button from copy URL to open URL could provide
more convenience for users to directly access user guide with a click.

Let's
* update the link to Mass Linkers user guide
* add a command summary
* allow user to open user guide directly in the browser with a button

after add and edit commands does not align with the user guide.

Ensuring the same order is used in both the app and the UG
could allow user to make cross-references more easily.

Let's update the order of parameters in the app.

to change our project direction.

UG should be constantly updated with new ideas and features to show
our progress and serve as guidelines when we implement the features.

User guide contains outdated UI mockup and features.

UG should be updated to reflect current mockup and features
to be followed during implementation.

Let's update UG to the current version.

captured and saved into data file.

Student is unable to unmark a taken mod as not taken for a batchmate,
so any accidental marking of mod previously could not be undone.

Adding a mod unmark function could allow student to
change and update the status of mods of a batchmate more easily.

Let's
* implement the mod unmark command
* add tests for mod unmark command
* update UG for mod mark and mod unmark to change some phrasing

commitResults.messageBody:
DG doesn't contain design details specific to Mass Linkers.

Documentation should be updated regularly to replace outdated
information with current ones and avoid unexpected problems
near the final submission deadline.

Let's update DG with the implementation of mod mark command.

Mod mark Activity Diagram contains a branch which seems unneccesary
with this representation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update DG mod mark activity diagram
commitResults.messageBody:
Activity diagram for mod mark contains the PlantUML
loop notation which is not taught or used in CS2103T module.

This should not be used and might be seen as a bug to future reviewers.

Let's update the activity diagram to replace that notation with
other appropriate notations allowed in CS2103T module.

commitResults.messageTitle: Mark all as taken: mod mark all
commitResults.messageBody:
A student is unable to mark module(s) of all batchmates as taken,
especially after one semester. Manually updating the status of a
specific module for all batchmates would be very time-consuming.

Adding a mod mark all command allows a student to conveniently
mark the specific module of all batchmates as taken.

Let's implement the mod mark all command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add error messages for invalid mods into mod mark all
commitResults.messageBody:
Prompt the student with error messages when one or more specified
mods are not found in all batchmates.

A student could only mark specified mods of all batchmates, which
may be inconvenient when student wants to update all mod status of
all batchmates at the end of each semester.

Allowing the student to mark all mods of all batchmates
with a single command would be more convenient to update mod status.

Let's change the mod mark all command from
mod mark all MODULE [MORE_MODULES]... to mod mark.
